                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d522">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.00/335: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-01T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 1, 1936—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>293. Your 377, July 28, 5 p.m. Personal and Confidential for the Ambassador.</p>
                <p>Are we correct in assuming that the recent announcement of the membership and
                    terms of reference of the Royal Commission of Inquiry indicates that the British
                    Government has abandoned, for the time being at least, any plans it may have had
                    to suspend temporarily Jewish immigration into Palestine? Any information you
                    can obtain discreetly as to the present status of this matter would be most
                    helpful.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
